Head (
Figs 1 A–B
). Temporal setae 23–25 . Eyes containing 3–4 terminal facets. Tentorium 223 ( 1 ) µm long, stipes not measurable. Clypeus 145–150 µm long, 103–125 µm wide at largest part, bearing 27–30 setae. Palpomere 1–5 lengths: 70 ( 1 ); 90 ; 140–155, 200 ; 325–330 µm. Antennal flagellum 1260–1360 µm long, diameter of pedicel 380 ( 1 ) µm, apical setae single (Fig. B), AR 1.96–2.23 .

Thorax (
Fig. 1 C
). Antepronotum with 6 lateral setae. Acrostichals 34–42 , biserial; dorsocentrals 29–32 ; prealars 9–11 ; supraalar 1 ( 1 ). Anapleural suture ratio 0.54–0.65 . Scutellum with 27–28 setae.

Wing (
Fig. 1 D
). Width 0.6 ( 1 ) mm. Costa 1.3 ( 1 ) mm long. WW 0.31 ( 1 ). All veins and membrane setose (not drawn). Brachiolum with 2 ( 1 ) setae. Squama with 23 ( 1 ) setae.

